Plummeting temperatures and thick fog caused delays and disruption for drivers in Glasgow today. In pictures: thick fog causes problems for Glasgow drivers Plummeting temperatures and thick fog caused delays and disruption for drivers in Glasgow today.Early morning drivers were caught out as thick fog blanketed the city.Traffic was slow and heavier than usual on the M8, M74 and M80 in North Lanarkshire, and there were a reports of accidents on roads in the area.Emergency services were called to a crash on the M77, at the Newton Mearns junction at around 8.30am.Traffic was brought to a standstill in Crow Road due to roadworks at the Clyde Tunnel.Temperatures dipped as low as 3C this morning, however, forecasters predict the fog will clear during the day with more cloud moving in over night.